de\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pap1665702674388.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pap1665702674388.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pap1665702674388.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pap1665702674388\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Generate a message after an inactive period.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"pap1665702674388__topic_d143405e1_d143406e1_d143407e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pap1665702674388__p_d143408e1_d143409e1_d143410e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$TIMEOUT</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} Minutes\n         </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pap1665702674388__section_m3y_sdc_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1136945e62\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"pap1665702674388__table_d17042e1_d17043e1_d17044e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Any application assignment file</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pap1665702674388__section_sqs_wdc_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1136945e108\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pap1665702674388__p_d143417e1_d143418e1_d143419e1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$TIMEOUT</span> generates a message after\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">Minutes</var> minutes have elapsed during which the user has not been active\n        in the application; a new message is generated after each period of\n          <var class=\"keyword varname\">Minutes</var> in which the user has not been active. You can set a maximum\n        value of 10080 minutes, which equals one week time.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pap1665702674388__p_d143420e1_d143421e1_d143422e1\">The message contains the string 'Timeout'. This\n        interrupt can be handled in a receiveMessage trigger, allowing the application to be closed\n        cleanly. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pap1665702674388__pre_cgy_zdc_xvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger receiveMessage \nif ($result = \"Timeout\")\n ; perform close-up activities\n ...\n apexit\nendif\nend; receiveMessage trigger\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pap1665702674388__p_d143426e1_d143427e1_d143428e1\">This setting is available only on Microsoft\n        Windows.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pap1665702674388__section_zbn_f2c_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle exampletitle\" id=\"pap1665702674388__p_d143429e1_d143430e1_d143431e1\">Example:\n        $TIMEOUT</h2>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pap1665702674388__pre_cxs_h2c_xvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[SETTINGS]\n$TIMEOUT = 20\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530844\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530844\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$TIMEOUT Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 09, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Generate a message after an inactive period. $TIMEOUT { = } Minutes Defaults Assignment file: Any application assignment file Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description $TIMEOUT generates a message after Minutes minutes have elapsed during which the user has not been active in the application; a new message is generated after each period of Minutes in which the user has not been active. You can set a maximum value of 10080 minutes, which equals one week time. The message contains the string 'Timeout'. This interrupt can be handled in a receiveMessage trigger, allowing the application to be closed cleanly. For example: trigger receiveMessage if ($result = \"Timeout\") ; perform close-up activities ... apexit endif end; receiveMessage trigger Copy This setting is available only on Microsoft Windows. Example: $TIMEOUT [SETTINGS] $TIMEOUT = 20 Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}